Words to live by. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I disagree. EQ servers and clients are based in five year old technology. A lot better mediums for web applications and upgrading have come out since then. Will SOE cave to its rival and use .NET in EQ2 and SWG is the question.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
While I don't profess to be a programming god, I really don't think the problem is what platform they use. .NET is just an XML platform, where the native code is win32. The reasons that the servers have to come down is that you can't push code while someone is actively trying to execute it, unless you want to wind up with a gosh-awful mess. .NET works fine for web-based applications where everything is done by discreet requests, but the same kind of logic just doesn't apply to real-time games. Imagine what happens when you have 3,000 people playing a game, and half of them are using one code base, and the others are using the other. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Plus, considering how piss-poor EQ performs today using (I assume) a primarily C++ base, can you imagine the new depths of sluggishness that .NET would achieve? Yeah, I know they say it isn't really interpretted for windows boxen, but....<br>
<br>
Oh, now for my pet-peeve: people taking smoking breaks during a group. It's just as bad as the gotta-get-KEI-brb thing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=caillougna>Caillou GNA</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pebble with a bow</span><br>  Posts: 1417<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/23/03 5:55:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3074.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: EQ PET PEVES</span><hr size=1> I hope they never go to some huge mess like .Net.  Bad enough I have to run Windows to play EQ, they could only make it worse by integrating that buggy, security laden mess on to it.<br>
<br>
But... that aside.  The issue is, as Stathol said, one of code base and who is on what part.  Web technologies can be transaction based (several are now and implement it better than... well.. anything Microsoft) but something like EQ can't really.   It would be hard to even have each zone in considered a transaction because you would have mobs acting differently to different people depending on what code base they were on.  For soloing that -might- work, but for groups or raids... an utter mess. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sabrosia>Sabrosia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lady of the Wolf<BR>Lady of the Silent Soul</span><br>  Posts: 81<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/23/03 6:02:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3074.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: EQ PET PEVES</span><hr size=1> Several people need a waaaahmbulance...<br>
